1:
Yahweh, I have come to you to be safe;
\q2 never allow me to become ashamed.
\q1

2:
Because you always do what is right, help me and rescue me;
\q2 listen to me, and save me!
\q1

5:
Yahweh, my Lord, you are the one whom I confidently expect to help me;
\q2 I have trusted in you ever since I was young.
\q1

9:
Now when I have become an old man, do not reject me;
\q2 do not abandon me now when I am not strong anymore.
\q1

10:
My enemies say that they want to kill me;
\q2 they talk together and plan how they can do that.
\q1

12:
God, do not stay far away from me;
\q2 hurry to help me!
\q1

16:
Yahweh, my Lord, I will praise you for your mighty deeds;
\q2 I will proclaim that only you always act justly.
\q1

19:
God, you do many righteous deeds;
\q2 it is as though they extend up to the sky.
\q1 You have done great things;
\q2 there is no one like you.
\q1
